entries.femaleVariant: Go on, take a look.
Really helped me out, V. You go ahead, I'll grab the rest of the files myself.
The hell's goin' on?
Hazed me once, won't do it again. Who the hell are you, really?
Wait, who the hell is this guy?
What's he talkin' about?
What's he talkin' about?
Can't you see he's threatening me? Militech murdered the scientist, now they're trying to murder me.
I gotta get this story out, or they'll kill everyone on the project, one by one.
What're you talkin' about?
Bree's just in it for the cred. Thing is, 'cause of her, they'll wipe anyone who touched the project.
He's just trying to scare us, V. You know that.
Think! You really wanna stick your neck out for her?
Sure do.
Bree! Cover, now!
[Take shard] What's this?
So, what now?
So, that's that?
All clear now.
Come on out.
Thanks, V. I mean it.
Pleased with yourself?
How's it feel, cowboy, pullin' triggers for a corp?
Heard a lotta insults in my day – try again if you wanna surprise me.
Stand back, merc.
Who the hell's this?
[Stand] Well, got what you wanted.
That was a million years ago.
Look, if it mattered, would've been old news years ago.
Kiddin' me? You hear about Soulkiller? Now imagine a similar project, only Militech's pushin' the buttons.
Sure you're not playing this up a little?
Like other peeps haven't tried to contact Blackwall AIs. Failin' to see the big break there.
Look, Voodoo Boys pokin' at the Blackwall is one thing. But one of the world's most powerful megacorps weaponizing a wild AI? Infinitely worse.
When people learn NetWatch is busy hunting ordinary Joes while giving the megacorps free reign? Imagine the outcry.
So, we got it? Grab what you need, let's delta.
Including you. Y'want that?
Wrong. It's 'cause of you Mijares got wiped. And what for, huh? The eddies?
Fuckin' hazed me. Can't believe she was only in it for the scratch.
Fuck. Really thought she was tryin' to do somethin' good.
Think I deserve something.
Better deal with this data.
So, the data – what's your plan? Saw the tapes, Militech was tryin' its damndest to breach the Blackwall...
Listen to a little voice of reason – forget, move on, live on.
What did Dante mean?
What he was sayin'... any truth to it?
Really? The man who just tried to kill us – you give a damn what he thinks?
And, well, I did it. Changed my life. Didn't know I had it in me, but here I am.
Yeah, I wrote some pulp garbage, sponsored articles. Rent doesn't pay itself.
So, don't you owe me somethin'? For my trouble?
Whaddaya mean?
Shit. The oldest ones are encrypted. But wait ...
There's some newer footage… Dated twenty sixty-eight.
Must be when they came back. C'mere, take a look.
Shit, this is bigger than I thought. Militech using some rogue AI to augment their old weaponry… This is huge!
Dante?!
Howdy, Bree.
Unbelievable. There's even files from the Third Corporate War here.
Yeah. Militech was tap-dancin' on its tits, tryin' to keep 'Saka from pushing 'em off the stage.
Knew Bree was hidin' in the area, knew you had somethin' to do with it. Just had to watch 'n' wait. Thanks, kid.
Hope you're not about to start defendin' her. Must've filled your head with all sorts of horseshit.
Said people like you were after her, were gonna kill her. Hired me to keep that from happenin'.
Bree can speak for herself.
Said you were chasing her.
Oh, pilgrim. She told you she was a media, right?
Bree can talk. Ask her yourself.
And what'll I hear? More lies. Spinnin' tall tales is her specialty.
You gotta believe me. He knows I'm close, he wants to stop me.
Another failure to communicate. You don't know my mind, but I sure as hell know yours, Bree.
C'mon, just zero him!
Dante Caruso, Militech Special Agent. Second class, mind you.
Give it a rest, Bree.
How's it you're here?
That quant you were pulling intel from, Caesar Mijares. Y'know they zeroed him, right?
Sorry, Bree. Lab ain't big enough for the both of us.
Stop him, V!
Not anymore.
Feelin' fuckin' stupid now.
Road to hell wouldn't be paved without good intentions, kid. Important thing's to head in the right direction once you see it.
Why'd you take your gig? Charity? Come on.
One more thing. Did me a solid, kid, deserve your cut.
Ehh, fine. Grab your cut.
Now get lost, kid. Gotta wait for all the data to wander home.
Li'l piece of advice, too. Believe in people, sure – but don't ever trust 'em.
How'd you know Dante?
But hey, I survived. And I'm gonna milk this chance for all it's worth.
Bettin' he had loads of people like me on his conscience.
What're you gonna do now?
Can't wait for the article.
What's the plan now?
Can't wait to read the article.
I publish, then I take a long vacation. Far, far away from anyone wantin' to find me, killer corporats especially.
Mhm – you'll be the first to know when it's ready.
And then I'll take a long vacation. Far, far away from anyone wantin' to find me, killer corporats especially.
What'm I lookin' at?
A log of all her convos with NetWatch. Bree planned to sell the lab data, grab the eddies and run. Like I said.
Still feelin' sorry for her?
Meanin', see for yourself.
Yeah. Only journalism she's ever done was to write articles rakin' muck at our competition.
Not lookin' for gratitude. Just an easy night's sleep.
It was her. She's the one who gave 'em Mijares.
Made the right choice.
If Bree printed this data, it'd set off a modern-day witch hunt. Who knows how many'd hang.
So Militech's going back to the lab?
Guessin' Militech aims to secure the project, resume research?
Truth be told, hope I'm dead 'n' gone before they do.
Maybe someday, sure. Not today, not tomorrow – makin' it not our problem.
Thing is, at some point you wake up and you realize you live in a dump and your life's a waste.
She tell you how she wrote articles for us, muckin' up the competition?
Max Jones, Bree Whitney... Dunno who hurt you, but you clearly got somethin' against the free press.
The bastards were tryin' to reopen the project.
Hear that? They wanted to breach the Blackwall!
These things change the world. And not for the better – least not for people like us.
Dante Caruso, Militech Special Agent. Stand down, I'm here for Bree. Couldn't give half a shit about you.
Knew she was hiding somewhere in the area, knew you were looking for her. Just had to watch 'n' wait. Thanks, kid.
You find yourself losin' sleep over it some day, well... just turn over onto your other side.
Now, gotta wait for all the data to wander home. Happy trails, kid.
You two deserve each other.
Shit, mighta guessed. Instead of fuckin' around with corp secrets, cobwebs an' dark corners, could've just said it was a corporat tiffle.
No, no, it wasn't like that. I wrote for Militech just to get access to their archives.
Ah, can see those gears churnin' now. Yeah, Bree worked for Militech.
That true, Bree?
That true?
Yes. Took the gigs, 'cause that meant I got access to their archives.
Know how you feel. Also left the corp behind, wasn't easy. But it gets better, I promise.
Know how you feel.
Yeah, countin' on it. Anyway, I'll finally be workin' for number one.
Think I'll take a long vacation first, though. Y'know, in case some suit decides to trail me again.
He steal your promotion or you klep his coffee mug?
Yeah, Militech an' some secret weapon, street's been sayin' it for ages... usually between "world's ending on Tuesday" and "Bartmoss is hibernatin' in a fridge."
You're lying.
I was undercover – took the gigs to get access to their archives.
Ran into the guy at your unit – who the fuck was he?
Who was that?
Did what you asked.
You and Dante – know each other well?
Nah, he was just another Militech wetworker. Cowboy who reined in anyone wantin' off the corpo leash.
Was supposed to be your huscle, so I was. Don't care to talk detes.
Good, 'cause there aren't any. The guy was just another corpo gun out to get me.
What'd he want?
Well, that's that.
Militech, special agent. Guess you really did step on some corp toes.
Told you the megacorps wanted to bury this story. No surprise they sent one of their own.
[Play file – REC_09/25/68.vid]
[Play file – REC_10/31/68.vid]
[Play file – REC_11/11/68.vid]
Were they running from the war? Or NetWatch...?
Unlike you, I'm tellin' the truth. How many lies did you have to spin to even get in here?
The truth? Heh… Mean the kind in those articles of yours muckin' up our competition?
Bunker the guy mentioned… Guessin' this lab was a Project Cynosure facility. One of many, most likely.
Project Cynosure… recognize the name.
For sure. We're talking a huge investment, gargantuan. Who knows how much tech's collecting rust in Dogtown's depths?
A flag in the wind's whatcha are. Whose pocket're you in right now? Arasaka, NetWatch?
Downloadin' loadin' loadin', get that data roamin', hm-hm, hm-hm, hm-hm, roamin'… hm-hm, hm-hm, hm-hm, mhm. Hm-hm, hm-hm, hm-hm, mhm. Hmmm, hm-hm, hm-hm, mhm.
What the...
